The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Thursday, September 18, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Thursday, September 18, 2003				 																Road to avoid				 																																	Chowringhee, between Park Street and Esplanade. A section barricaded for the construction of a flyover.				 																Seminar				 																																	Encountering Theory: Three Decades of the Humanities Experiment at Jadavpur University, 10 am.				 																																	Prof J.A. Mangan will speak on Imperial Sport as the Stylised Epitome of a Moral Metaphor at Calcutta University, Alipore campus, from 11 am. Kaushik Banerjee to talk on Sports History in India: Problems and Prospects at 12.30 pm, and Boria Majumdar on Commercial Revolution in Indian Cricket, at 2.30 pm.				 																Silk show				 																																	Silk Fab, an exhibition of silk products, to be inaugurated at Swabhumi, 3 pm.				 																Exhibition				 																																	Art in Life, an exhibition of Indian handicrafts, and clothes and accessories by designer Sabyasachi Mukherjee, at CIMA Gallery, 11 am to 8 pm.				 																Tribute				 																																	Amader Satinath, a tribute to Satinath Chatterjee, at Bangla Akademi, from 6 pm. Mahasveta Devi, Debesh Ray and Geeta Ghatak to participate.				 																Art watch				 																																	Chairs, an exhibition of recent works by K.G. Subramanyan, at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 2 pm to 7.30 pm.				 																Photo				 																																	Sri Aurobindo Institute of Culture presents an exhibition of photographs by Amal Sengupta at Galerie la Mere from 4 pm to 7 pm.
